  "body": "The following code triggers an issue when using a combination of `chai-as-promised`, the explicit inclusion of `ethereum-waffle` and the use of solidity `selfdestruct`.\r\n\r\nI'll include code for the issue and the failure below, but I've also created a simple repo that displays the problem at https://github.com/hkalodner/buidler-issue/\r\n\r\nI resolved the issue by removing the explicit call to `use(solidity)`, but I suspect there may be some more core issue based on the mysterious way the error is occurring (removing the `selfdestruct` or the use of `chai-as-promised` also fixed the issue`).\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity ^0.5.11;\r\n\r\ncontract Test {\r\n\r\n    string public constant test = \"test\";\r\n\r\n    function shutdown() external {\r\n        selfdestruct(msg.sender);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst { expect, use } = require('chai')\r\nconst chaiAsPromised = require(\"chai-as-promised\")\r\nconst { solidity } = require('ethereum-waffle')\r\n\r\nuse(chaiAsPromised)\r\nuse(solidity)\r\n\r\ndescribe('Test', () => {\r\n  it('test should succeed', async function () {\r\n    const Test = await ethers.getContractFactory('Test')\r\n    const test = await Test.deploy()\r\n    await test.deployed()\r\n    await expect(test.test()).to.eventually.equal(\"test\")\r\n    await test.shutdown()\r\n  })\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nI get the following error when running the test against in internal node `yarn buidler test`, but not when running against an external node `yarn buidler --network localhost test`\r\n\r\n `Uncaught RuntimeError: abort(Error: call revert exception (method=\"test()\", errorSignature=null, errorArgs=[null], reason=null, code=CALL_EXCEPTION, version=abi/5.0.5)). Build with -s ASSERTIONS=1 for more info.`\r\n\r\n",
